Eleanor is a (foster) mom again, and our hearts are absolutely broken for our new family member. Meet Alivia- she was found, barely alive, in rural Iowa. An amazing passerby spotted her and took her to the local shelter- @paws.and.more . As you can see, Alivia is severely emaciated and has sores on her body that suggest she might have been living in her own filth. Because of her condition, she also started having seizures. We don’t know her age, we don’t truly know her background but we do know that this sweet girl was so lucky to have been found and we are beyond honored to be fostering her. Please send all of your love and thoughts her way- since she has a long way to go on her healing journey.

#fosterdog #fosteringsaveslives #rescuedog

*sad photo if you swipe* Alivia settled in so well with our family yesterday!  She has the sweetest personality and hasn’t let what happened to her in her past affect her ability to love and trust 💙 She currently weighs 19lb, 12oz and hasn’t had any additional seizures since the day she was rescued. We can’t wait to see this girl grow and get up to a healthy weight!

Surprising absolutely no one… Alivia (now known as Mila) is officially home with us 🖤 She has actually been “ours” for about two weeks now, but she still has some vet work to get done so we wanted to hold off on saying anything. 

If you’ve known us for any amount of time, then you know that puppies have never really been our thing. We typically adopt the seniors, the hospice and the scared/puppy mill dogs. And, believe it or not, adopting her wasn’t in our initial plan 🫣

When Mila came to us, she was so skinny that we were scared that the damage that had been done was too much for her little body to overcome. The first few days we actually wondered if she was going to be a hospice foster. Watching our dogs step in was nothing short of amazing though. Mose, Lola and Eleanor stepped up to take care of her in a way that only they could. They snuggled her, gently played with her, taught her to trust and took this little babe into their hearts like she had been there all along. Eleanor, specifically, has become a puppy herself and spends hours playing with Mila. 

After losing our two seniors within weeks of each other, our house just hasn’t been the same. Mila has brought so much life back into our home that we couldn’t imagine saying goodbye to her and we know our pups feel the same way. 

Welcome home, Mila 💙 We love you so much and are so excited to be able to watch you grow up!

Today is National Puppy Mill Survivor Day and we are blessed to share our home and hearts with two amazing souls who were rescued from an incredibly cruel industry. 

Both Eleanor and Lola were bred when they were only puppies themselves and existed just so humans could profit. 

The fact is that people fund puppy mills. 

When you buy a puppy from a pet store or from a website without doing your research, the odds that you are financially investing in a puppy mill are very high. 

Neither of our girls deserved to suffer the way that they did, no one ever should. Please do your part and adopt your next best friend or do extensive research before you buy. 

And please don’t forget to share Eleanor’s story and tell everyone you know about puppy mills 💛🖤

Eleanor suffered in a puppy mill for no reason. She barely survived her nightmare just so people could profit. If you plan on buying a dog, please research the breeder before you buy. Google them, ask @bailing_out_benji  for the records, visit the parents to see how they live, ask for the OFA tests. Do your part to make sure your puppy’s parents aren’t suffering. 

At our house, we prefer to rescue dogs like Eleanor, Mose, Lola and Mila 💛 If that sounds like you, then please check out petfinder.com and search for your breed of choice! 

#adoptadog #researchbeforeyoubuy #goldenretriever #endpuppymills

#kitten #goldenretriever #bestfriends

So Moira is staying for us for a little bit… 💛🖤 Yes, we gave her a name! Moira didn’t have anywhere else to go and we don’t have any kitties currently that can catch her upper respiratory infection. That is a very contagious disease for kitties and putting her in a home with other cats or asking a rescue agency to take a contagious medical case on would have been irresponsible for us to do when we have the means to care for her. So Moira stays until she’s healthy and then we will see what a future forever family looks like for her! Welcome to the fam, little one. Our crew is thrilled to have you! And Eleanor is thrilled to be a foster mama once again! She has “fostered” two puppies, adopted a sick puppy {Mila}, and is now taking on her first sick kitty case! 

Eleanor to the rescue! 

#kitten #rescuedog #goldenretriever #puppymillsurvivor
